<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 1848" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1848" box="[976,1392,2542,2571]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opimus">Ctenomys opimus Wagner, 1848</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="516">“Bolivia.” Restricted by O. Thomas in 1900 to “Sahama,” Mont Sahama, Oruro, about 17°49’ S, 67°28” W, 3000-4000 m.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[806,1398,2542,2964]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1848" box="[809,1032,2700,2729]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opimus">Ctenomys opimus</taxonomicName>
was initially included in Chaco group, but according to mtDNA analysis, it belongs to the opimusspecies group. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 26 and FN = 48, and sperm is symmetric. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
